  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-03-10",
    "date": "2021-05-21T16:36:47Z",
    "text": "Hold Congress Accountable Act\n\nThis bill withholds or eliminates the pay of Members of Congress during a government shutdown.\n\nThrough the day of the general election in November 2022, any salary earned by Members during a government shutdown must be held in escrow and released on the last day of the 117th Congress.\n\nAfter the November 2022 general election, a Member shall not be paid for any day during which the government is shut down."
  },
